## 7. Item catalog (reference)

### 7.1 The Blessing of Shieldon

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Exploration (meta-item) |
| Lifecycle | Single-use → consumed |
| Passive | +10% SPD |
| Skill | **Single use.** Enchant the `Possession` tag onto a target wonder item in your inventory. The Blessing is then consumed. Cannot target `Eternal` items. |
| CD | — (single use) |
| Tags | — |

### 7.2 THE VOID

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Hybrid (exploration passive, combat skill) |
| Lifecycle | Static (permanent burden) |
| Passive | **`Eternal` `Possession`.** Every 4 days, a **VOID PHANTOM** spawns on the overworld map. The player's vision is shared by all phantoms — they see what you see. Each time the player enters a new node, all phantoms move one step toward the player's position. |
| Skill | **Combat only.** All foes lose their vision for 10 seconds. |
| CD | 2 days (day-based) |
| Tags | `Possession`, `Eternal` |

> **Design note:** THE VOID is a cursed item — once acquired, it cannot be removed.
> The phantoms create escalating map pressure: the more you explore, the closer they get.
> When a phantom reaches the player's position, it triggers a **BOSS fight** at that node.
> (Phantom contact mechanics are deferred to a future content pass — the spawning and
> movement rules are kept as placeholders.)

### 7.3 DD

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Hybrid |
| Lifecycle | Static |
| Passive | Each time you pick up a wonder core, heal 2% of max HP. |
| Skill | **Combat.** Release DD — a small bug-like creature that **crouches** on the ground. DD moves along the ground dealing **200 damage** to everything in its path. It turns around on hitting a wall. The player must **reclaim** DD (walk into it) to stow it again. |
| CD | 2 days (day-based) |
| Tags | — |

> **Design note:** The game does not pause when a combat node's goal is achieved or
> the timer expires — DD can still be reclaimed during the post-combat window. If the
> player leaves the node without reclaiming DD, it is **set free** (lost permanently).
> The item is removed from inventory. Don't forget to claim it back.

### 7.4 Pome's Bravery

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Hybrid |
| Lifecycle | Single-use → Convertible |
| Passive | OnFire duration +0.2 s. While OnFire: **+5% omni-vamp** (lifesteal on all damage dealt). |
| Skill | **Single use.** Set oneself on fire (60 OnFire stacks). After use, converts to **Pome's Seed**. |
| CD | — (single use) |
| Tags | `Convertible` |

### 7.5 Pome's Seed

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Exploration (plantable) |
| Lifecycle | Plantable → harvest |
| Passive | OnFire duration +0.2 s. While OnFire: +5% omni-vamp. |
| Skill | — (dormant skill slot) |
| CD | — |
| Tags | `Plantable` |
| Harvest time | **4 days** |
| Fruit | **1–3× Pome's Bravery** (quantity rolled at harvest). Each Bravery's stats are **randomized** independently — the father's attributes are not inherited; each fruit rolls fresh. |

### 7.6 FanChen's Heart

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Combat |
| Lifecycle | Static |
| Passive | While Frozen: restore **30% of post-mitigation direct damage** received from enemies (effectively: Frozen = lifesteal against incoming hits). |
| Skill | **Combat.** Grant oneself 60 Frozen stacks. |
| CD | 30 s (second-based) |
| Tags | — |

### 7.7 Yukai's Rope

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Combat |
| Lifecycle | Static |
| Passive | While in the air: **+30 DEF**. |
| Skill | **Combat.** Fire a rope 80 m forward. On hitting an obstacle (wall, ground, platform), the player is **dragged** to the impact point. |
| CD | 30 s (second-based) |
| Tags | — |

### 7.8 Pixolotl's Feather

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Hybrid |
| Lifecycle | Single-use → Convertible |
| Passive | Gravity reduced by **20%**. |
| Skill | **Map — single use.** Flash back to **one day earlier** (undo the current day's consequences: stamina spent, damage taken, node entered — exact undo scope TBD). Then converts to **Pixolotl's Wish**. |
| CD | — (single use) |
| Tags | `Convertible` |

> **Design note:** "Flash back one day" is a powerful time-rewind mechanic. The scope
> of what gets undone (day counter? VOID devour? item cooldowns? foe levels?) needs
> precise specification before implementation. The safest interpretation: the day
> counter does **not** rewind (time only flows forward for the VOID), but the player's
> position, HP, and stamina revert to their start-of-day state.

### 7.9 Pixolotl's Wish

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Exploration (plantable) |
| Lifecycle | Plantable → harvest |
| Passive | Gravity reduced by **20%**. |
| Skill | — (dormant skill slot) |
| CD | — |
| Tags | `Plantable` |
| Harvest time | 7 days |
| Fruit | 2× **Pixolotl's Feather** |

### 7.10 The Forgotten Kashaya

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Combat |
| Lifecycle | Static |
| Passive | On a **melee attack hit**: bounce back **50% of post-mitigation damage** dealt to the target (thorns/reflect). |
| Skill | **Combat.** Knock back all enemies within 4 m. Deals **10 damage**. |
| CD | 15 s (second-based) |
| Tags | — |

### 7.11 QiongFeng Emperor of LOONG's Claw

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Exploration |
| Lifecycle | Conditional trigger → consumed |
| Passive | When the player **defeats the current world's LV4 boss**: immediately loot all **unopened chests** in that world. After looting, the world **cracks down** (becomes inaccessible — all its nodes are treated as devoured). The claw then **faints** (is removed from inventory). The player is **teleported to a still-existing shelter node** (one that has not been devoured). If no such shelter exists, the player is teleported to **a level-5 node in zone 6**. |
| Skill | — |
| CD | — |
| Tags | `Convertible` (consumed on trigger) |

> **Design note:** "Chests" and "domain" are future content. For now, "domain" = the
> current outer world, and "unopened chests" = combat/function nodes the player
> skipped. The world-crack is a dramatic irreversible action — use wisely.

### 7.12 A Weird Mushroom

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Hybrid |
| Lifecycle | Perishable → Convertible, OR Single-use → random outcome |
| Passive | **`Perishable` (2 days).** If not used within 2 days, converts to **A Rotten Mushroom**. |
| Skill | **Single use.** Increase max HP and current HP by **20%**. **The next day** (from start to end of that day), one random effect occurs. The player does **not** know the outcome before eating — the effect is revealed the following day. |

| Outcome | Probability | Effect (lasts the entire next day unless stated otherwise) |
|---------|------------|--------|
| (a) | 18% | Lose 40% HP (−20% from the original base) |
| (b) | 18% | Left/right movement controls swap for one day |
| (c) | 18% | Movement speed +300% for one day |
| (d) | 18% | Jump height +300% for one day |
| (e) | 18% | Gain an extra 20% HP (stacks with the initial +20%; permanent) |
| (f) | 10% | The protagonist who ate it can carry **one extra wonder item** (held slot +1, permanent) |

| CD | — (single use) |
| Tags | `Perishable`, `Convertible` |

### 7.13 A Rotten Mushroom

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Domain | Exploration (plantable) |
| Lifecycle | Plantable → harvest |
| Passive | — |
| Skill | — |
| CD | — |
| Tags | `Plantable` |
| Harvest time | 4 days |
| Fruit | 4× **A Weird Mushroom**. Each fruit inherits the father's max-HP modifier in the range **60%–140%**. Unlike the wild mushroom, each fruit has a **clearly labeled consequence** (a–f) visible before eating — the consequence is an **inheritable trait** determined at harvest time, rolled independently per fruit. |

